dfischer.utils

Class DataCollectionSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.DataCollectionSet

  • public class DataCollectionSet
extends java.lang.Object
    Contains a combination of one or several data collection sequences which are dynamically measured on the fly during load test execution. Data collection sequences can be added at runtime during load test execution.
    See Also:
    DataCollectionSequence, DataCollectionFloatItem, DataCollectionYZFloatItem, DataCollectionTextItem, DataCollectionErrorEventItem

    • Method Detail

      • addDataCollectionSequence

        public int addDataCollectionSequence(java.lang.String diagramTitle,
                            java.lang.String diagramSubTitle,
                            java.lang.String yAxisLabel,
                            java.lang.Object sequenceContext)
        Create a new data collection sequence and add it to this set. Used for data collections of ITEM_TYPE_FLOAT_VALUE and ITEM_TYPE_TEXT_FRAGMENT.
        Parameters:
        diagramTitle - GUI diagram title
        diagramSubTitle - GUI diagram subtitle (optional, can be an empty string)
        yAxisLabel - GUI diagram Y-axis label (optional, can be an empty string or null)
        sequenceContext - optional foreign context for this data collection sequence, can be null - and will not be serialized
        Returns:
        the unique ID of the new data collection sequence. Note: the ID is only unique per instance of this class - but not overall instances of this class.
        See Also:
        DataCollectionFloatItem, DataCollectionTextItem

      • addDataCollectionSequence

        public int addDataCollectionSequence(java.lang.String diagramTitle,
                            java.lang.String diagramSubTitle,
                            int xyzGuiDisplayHint,
                            java.lang.String yAxisLabel,
                            java.lang.String zAxisLabel,
                            java.lang.Object sequenceContext)
        Create a new data collection sequence and add it to this set. Used for data collections of ITEM_TYPE_YZ_FLOAT_VALUE
        Parameters:
        diagramTitle - GUI diagram title
        diagramSubTitle - GUI diagram subtitle (optional, can be an empty string)
        xyzGuiDisplayHint - controls which diagram type is shown by the GUI (XY, XZ, or YZ)
        yAxisLabel - GUI diagram Y-axis label (optional, can be an empty string or null)
        zAxisLabel - GUI diagram Z-axis label (optional, can be an empty string or null)
        sequenceContext - optional foreign context for this data collection sequence, can be null - and will not be serialized
        Returns:
        the unique ID of the new data collection sequence. Note: the ID is only unique per instance of this class - but not overall instances of this class.
        See Also:
        DataCollectionYZFloatItem, DataCollectionYZFloatItem.DISPLAY_HINT_DIAGRAM_TYPE_XY, DataCollectionYZFloatItem.DISPLAY_HINT_DIAGRAM_TYPE_XZ, DataCollectionYZFloatItem.DISPLAY_HINT_DIAGRAM_TYPE_YZ

      • addDataCollectionSequence

        public void addDataCollectionSequence(DataCollectionSequence dataCollectionSequence,
                             int newSequenceId)
        Add a data collection sequence to this set and set a new sequence id.
        Note: a RuntimeException is thrown if another data collection sequence with the same ID as the new sequence ID is already stored in this set.
        Parameters:
        dataCollectionSequence - data collection sequence to add
        newSequenceId - the new sequence id

        Add a new measured float value (real number) to a data collection sequence.
        Parameters:
        sequenceId - unique ID of the data collection sequence (returned by #addDataCollectionSequence())
